title: ghost_in_the_shell
body:
[b][i]Ghost in the Shell[/i][/b] ([i]Kōkaku Kidōtai[/i], literally [i]"Mobile Armored Riot Police"[/i]) is a Japanese multimedia [[science fiction]] and [[mecha]] [[cyberpunk]] franchise created in 1989 by [[Shirow Masamune]]. It is comprised of: Shirow's original manga (1989/1991, 2002 and 2003); two animated films (1995 and 2004) directed by Mamoru Oshii; two anime series ([[Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex]] in 2002-2003 and [i]Ghost in the Shell: S.A.C. 2nd Gig[/i] in 2004-2005), and their sequel OVA ([i]Ghost in the Shell: S.A.C. Solid State Society[/i] in 2006); as well as several video games and novels.

The series focuses on the activities of the counter-terrorist organization [[police|Public Security Section 9]] (公安9課), set in a futuristic, [[cyberpunk]] Japan.

An American live action adaptation was released in [[ghost in the shell (2017)|2017]]. The movie is directed by Rupert Sanders and written by Jamie Moss, William Wheeler and Ehren Kruger. The film stars [[Scarlett Johannson]], [[Kitano Takeshi]], Michael Pitt, Pilou Asbæk, Chin Han and Juliette Binoche. 

h4. Entries
* [[Ghost in the Shell: Innocence]]
* [[Ghost in the Shell 2: Man Machine Interface]]
* [[Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex]]
** [[Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex - First Assault Online]]
** [[Ghost in the Shell: SAC 2045]]
* [[Ghost in the Shell Arise]]
* [[Ghost in the Shell (2017)]]

h4. Characters

[b]Main Characters[/b]
* Major [[Kusanagi Motoko]], squad leader of Section 9's anti-terrorist unit
* [[Batou (gits)|]], the major's partner
* [[Togusa (gits)|]], an ex-police inspector
* Chief [[Aramaki Daisuke]], Executive Director of Section 9

[b]Secondary Characters[/b]
* [[Ishikawa (gits)|]]
* [[Saitou (gits)|]]
* [[Paz (gits)|]]
* [[Boma (gits)|]]

[b]Additional Characters[/b]
* [[Fuchikoma]]
* [[Tachikoma]]
* [[Laughing Man (gits)|]]
* [[Kuze Hideo]]
* [[Project 2501]]

h4. See also

* [[Ghost in the Shell lineup]]

h4. External Links
* "Wikipedia: Ghost in the Shell":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghost_in_the_Shell

title: movie_camera
body:
A camera that captures a rapid succession of pictures onto film.  By playing the film in an appropriate projector, the images can be viewed in rapid succession to produce an animated picture of what was originally viewed by the camera.  

Not to be confused with the [[camcorder]] tag, which is a portable device that is composed of a video camera and video recorder. These devices use electronic motion picture acquisition, instead taking a rapid sequence of photos to film, and tend to look very different.

h4. See Also

* [[camera]] 
* [[video camera]]

title: tv_camera
body:
A large professional high-end video camera used by television studios and other businesses or organizations that need such devices.  Three major types of these are: studio cameras, Electronic News Gathering (ENG) cameras (like those used with field reporters), and Electronic Field Production (EFP) cameras (likes those used to broadcast professional sports). 

Only ENG cameras have the ability to record, making them similar to consumer [[camcorder]]s, although they tend to be much larger, heavier, and have a variety of other differences.  Studio and EFP cameras lack the ability to record anything and are tethered by cables to the other equipment that records and/or transmits the video for broadcasting.

h4. See also

* [[camera]] 
* [[movie camera]] 
* [[video camera]]

title: green_screen
body:
The most common form (and color) of chroma key compositing, used in various film and picture media to help composite items into other scenes, usually by selecting the color and replacing it with the intended background. 

While solid green is the most used color, any color with the same intent to help composite images can be used.


h4. See also

* [[Green Background]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Chroma Key":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chroma_key

title: mass_for_the_dead
body:
Mass for the Dead is a smartphone game developed by Exys Inc., and based on Kugane Maruyama's [[overlord (maruyama)|Overlord]] novel series. The website to pre-register for the game opened on June 25, 2018. The opening theme for the game was released on August 30, 2018 in a video promoting pre-registration. The game is free to play with in-app purchases. the game was made available for iOS and Android. 

On February 13, 2019, it was announced that the game app would be available on February 21, 2019. On March 31, 2021, Mass for the Dead was removed from the app stores but the game is still available for download in Japan.

body:
[[pokemon_(creature)|Pokémon]] #0018 in the National Pokédex, a Normal/Flying-type.

An avian Pokémon with large [[wings]], sharp [[talons]], and a short, hooked [[beak]]. Its glossy plumage is mostly brown with cream-colored underparts and flight feathers. Its head is decorated with a red and yellow crest that is nearly as long as its body. The fan-like feathers of its tail are red. Its beak and legs are pink, and there are angular black markings around its eyes.

Evolves from [[Pidgeotto]] (from [[Pidgey]]). It can also [[mega_pokemon|Mega Evolve]].

title: raihan_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Raihan[/b], known as [b]Kibana[/b] in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon swsh|Pokémon Sword and Shield]][/i].

Said to be the strongest Gym Leader in Galar, this Trainer has an easygoing personality that quickly changes to a fiery determination to win once he starts to battle [tn](official bio)[/tn]. His signature Pokémon is [[Duraludon]].

He has [[dark-skinned male|dark skin]], [[tareme|droopy]] [[aqua eyes]], and [[short hair|short]] [[undercut]] [[black hair]]. He wears an [[orange headband]], [[earrings]], a [[collared shirt]] under a [[black hoodie]], a [[dynamax band]], [[single glove|a]] [[partially fingerless gloves|glove]], [[side slit shorts]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]].

title: bellflower
body:
The bellflowers belong to the [i]Campanulaceae[/i] family of plants, which comprises around 2,000 species. They vary gteatly in color and details. The leaves are simple and alternating, while the flowers are bell-shaped and consist of a narrow lobed corolla.

Not to be confused with [[lily of the valley]], which has a shorter, rounder bell-shaped flower.

title: pidgeotto
body:
[[pokemon_(creature)|Pokémon]] #0017 in the National Pokédex, a Normal/Flying-type.

A raptor-like avian Pokémon. It is covered with [[brown feathers]], and has a cream-colored face and underside. It has a crest of pinkish-red feathers on its head and black, angular markings behind its eyes. The plumage of its tail has alternating [[red_feathers|red]] and [[yellow feathers]] with ragged tips. Its beak and legs are pink, and it has sharp [[talons]].

Evolves from [[Pidgey]], and into [[Pidgeot]].

Japanese name: [b]Pigeon[/b]

h4. Official art
* !post #9358324

h4. External links

* "Bulbapedia":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pidgeotto_%28Pokémon%29

title: four_of_a_kind_(touhou)
body:
[[Flandre Scarlet]]'s third [[spell card]] in [[Touhou]]'s [[Embodiment of Scarlet Devil]] Extra Stage that creates three copies of her. 

Sometimes activated to cause a bit of commotion around the [[Scarlet Devil Mansion]] to play around with the inhabitants. While canonically the copies are identical, it is common in fanwork for them to be given different personalities and/or variable appearance.

Tag only when three or more clones are present together, (unless [[odd one out|another character is replacing a clone]] such as, post #993825 or post #265820.) If there are two present, use [[clone]] and [[multiple persona]] instead.

For the poker hand the spell card is named after, see [[four of a kind (poker)]].

title: sequential
body:
For events happening in the image to happen one after the other in order (slightly similar to the sequential frames of a film movie).

This is different from [[time lapse]] in that a much shorter period of time (seconds) passes between each “frame”/event in the image.

Similar to [[sequential exposures]], which shows a sequence of moving object(s) all within a single frame.

h4. See Also

* [[flowchart]]
* [[progression]]
* [[multiple views]]
* [[boustrophedon order ]]

title: sequential_exposures
body:
A photography technique whereby a camera is used to capture an object in motion all within a single frame.

Different from [[sequential]] which shows a sequence of events that don't necessarily correspond to the same frame.

h4. See also

* [[time lapse]]
* [[multiple views]]

title: fate/stay_night
body:
An eroge by [[Type-Moon]], released in January 2004 and made into a 24-episode TV anime in 2006. The game is the first installment of the [[Fate (series)|]] franchise.

Original character designs and most official art made by [[Takeuchi Takashi]].

Consists of three divergent routes, each focusing on a different heroine:

* [[Fate/Stay Night]] - [[Saber (fate)|]]
* [[Fate/Unlimited Blade Works]] - [[Tohsaka Rin]]
* [[Heaven's Feel]] - [[Matou Sakura]]

Note that the above route tags should only be used when the pictures specifically mention said route, or when they show an event that only appears in it. 

The sequel is [[Fate/Hollow Ataraxia]].

title: sky_striker_ace_-_camellia
body:
[b]Link Rating[/b]: 2
[b]Link Arrows[/b]: Bottom-Left, Top-Right
[b]Attribute[/b]: Dark
[b]Type[/b]: Machine / Link / Effect
[i]2 Effect Monsters
Must first be Link Summoned. You can only Special Summon "Sky Striker Ace - Camellia(s)" once per turn. Once per turn, if you have 3 or less Spells in your GY: You can send 1 "Sky Striker" card from your Deck to the GY. If this card is sent to the GY: You can target 1 monster your opponent controls; Special Summon this card to your opponent's field (but shift control to its owner during the End Phase of this turn), and if you do, send that targeted monster to the GY.[/i]

[b]ATK[/b]: 1500

A [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]] [[duel monster]], Camellia is [[Sky Striker Ace - Raye|Raye]]'s rival in the card lore.

title: sky_striker_ace_-_roze
body:
[b]Level:[/b] 4
[b]Attribute:[/b] Light
[b]Type:[/b] Warrior / Effect
[i]If a "Sky Striker Ace" monster(s) is Normal or Special Summoned, except "Sky Striker Ace - Roze" (except during the Damage Step): You can Special Summon this card from your hand. If an opponent's monster in the Extra Monster Zone is destroyed by battle, or leaves the field because of your card effect, while this card is in your GY: You can Special Summon this card, then you can negate the effects of 1 face-up monster your opponent controls, until the end of this turn. You can only use each effect of "Sky Striker Ace - Roze" once per turn.[/i]

[b]ATK:[/b] 1500
[b]DEF:[/b] 1500

A [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]] [[duel monster]], Roze is [[Sky Striker Ace - Raye|Raye]]'s rival-turned-friend in the card lore.

She's the ace fighter of Spectra, the enemy of Raye's homeland of Karma and the pilot of the mecha [[sky_striker_ace_-_zeke|Zeke]]. It is later revealed in the [i]Yu-Gi-Oh! OCG Stories[/i] manga that she is one of the three [[android|androids]]/clones created specifically to counter Raye's "Sky Striker", the other being [[sky_striker_ace_-_azalea|Azalea]] and [[sky_striker_ace_-_camellia|Camellia]].

title: shotgun
body:
A [[gun]] that fires [[shotgun shell|shells]] containing pellets, rifled slugs, or other munitions. Shotguns have short effective range but high close-range destructive power due to the spread of the pellets. Shotguns generally have smoothbore barrels for firing multiple projectiles at once or in quick succession. There are numerous types of shotguns in different designs and configurations, such as:
* [[double-barreled shotgun|double-barrelled shotgun]] [tn](traditionally [[break action]])[/tn]
* [[bullpup]]
* [[lever action]]
* [[pump action]]
* [[sawed-off shotgun|sawn-off shotgun]]
* [[underbarrel shotgun]]

title: blade_runner_(series)
body: Blade Runner is an American cyberpunk media franchise originating from the 1968 novel [[Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?]] by Philip K. Dick, featuring the character of [[Rick Deckard]]. The book has been adapted into several media, including films, comics, a stage play, and a radio serial. The first film adaptation was [[Blade Runner (1982 movie)|]], directed by Ridley Scott in 1982. Although the film initially underperformed at the American box office, it became a cult classic, and has had a significant influence on [[science fiction]]. A novelization and a comic adaptation of the film were released in the same year. From 1995 to 2000, three novels serving as sequels to both Blade Runner and the original novel were written by K. W. Jeter, a friend of Dick's. A film sequel to Blade Runner, [[Blade Runner 2049]], was released in 2017. To celebrate the 30th anniversary of Blade Runner in 2012, a short film was released, and in the lead up to the release of Blade Runner 2049, several more short films detailing events that occurred between 2019 and 2049 were released. The influence of the franchise has helped spawn the [[cyberpunk]] subgenre.

title: tashkent_(azur_lane)
body:
[i][[Azur Lane]][/i]'s personification of the one-off Soviet large destroyer [i]Tashkent[/i]. 
Character design by [[Kincora]].

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[purple hair]] and [[blue eyes]].

Her default outfit consists of heavy [[winter clothes]]: a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[white coat|white]] [[duffel coat]] with [[fur trim]], [[earmuffs]], light brown [[sweater dress]] underneath, and white [[thigh boots]].

Her [[rigging]] consists of two 130 mm twin gun mounts and 533 mm triple [[torpedo tubes]].

h4. Skins

* !post #3801573: Default
* !post #3802302:  [[tashkent (the bound cruiser) (azur lane)|The Bound Cruiser]]
* !post #4381151:  [[tashkent (the blue snoozer) (azur lane)|The Blue Snoozer]]
* !post #7648943: [[tashkent (the sprite's snapshot) (azur lane)|The Sprite's Snapshot]]

h4. Alternative versions

* !post #4184899:  [[tashkent (muse) (azur lane)|Muse]]

h4. History

The [i]Tashkent[/i]-class of destroyers consisted of a single destroyer leader, built in Italy for the Soviet navy just before World War II. Three other ships were ordered but canceled before construction. The class is named after Tashkent, "the capital city":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tashkent] of Uzbekistan, under Soviet rule at that time.

Ultimately, the Soviets found out that it was impossible to adapt Italian shipbuilding practices with the comparatively inferior state of Soviet shipbuilding, so [i][[Kiev (Azur Lane)|]][/i] was designed as a cheaper version of [i]Tashkent[/i] but carrying the same armament.

One of her in-game skills is named [i]The Blue Cruiser[/i], a reference to how she was delivered to the Soviets in the [i]Regia Marina[/i]'s interwar paint scheme of bluish-gray overall.

h4. See also
* [[Tashkent (Kancolle)]]
* [[Tashkent (Warship Girls R)]]

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: [i]Tashkent[/i]":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_destroyer_Tashkent]

title: hinomoto_reiko
body:
The protagonist of [i][[Rumble Roses]][/i]. Voiced by [[Hidaka Noriko]]. Her Heel version is [[Rowdy Reiko]].

Reiko enters the Rumble Roses tournament after her mother and sister disappear.

Reiko has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]], [[brown eyes]], and [[medium breasts]], the left one having a [[mole on breast|mole]]. Her wrestling outfit consists of a [[red choker]] (sometimes a [[red scarf|scarf]] in illustrations), a [[red bikini]] top, [[red gloves|red]] [[fingerless gloves]], [[red shorts|red]] [[short shorts]], and [[red footwear|red]] [[knee boots]] that are [[cross-laced footwear|cross-laced]]. Her shorts are [[open fly|unzipped]], revealing her [[white panties]].

The first kanji on Reiko's name, "零", means "zero", which is alluded in her outfit, as both her panties and bikini top have the word "Zero" on them.

When fighting in a [[swimsuit]], she wears a [[front-tie bikini top|front]] and [[side-tie bikini bottom|side-tie]] [[polka dot bikini|polka-dotted]] [[white bikini]] and [[white sandals|white]] [[high heel sandals]].

title: evelyn_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Evelyn[/b], known as [b]Lesoir[/b] (ルスワール) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon xy|XY]][/i].

The third-born of the four [[Battle Chatelaine]] sisters, she has a very [[shy]] personality but very real skill. In the Battle Maison, she is in charge of Double Battles [tn](official bio)[/tn].

She has [[blue eyes]] and [[medium hair|shoulder-length]] [[blue hair]]. She wears a  [[blue headwear|blue]] [[top hat]] [[themed object|shaped like]] a rose, a [[blue dress|blue]] [[strapless dress]] which leaves her [[bare shoulders|shoulders bare]], [[black gloves|black]] [[elbow gloves]], a [[detached collar|blue collar]], [[black pantyhose]], and [[white shoes|white]] [[pumps]].

h4. See also

** [[Morgan (pokemon)|]] (sisters)

Sawyer is one of the retainers for [[Lear (pokemon)|]]’s royal family and head of the PML staff. He looks scary but is actually quite sentimental [tn](official bio)[/tn].

title: gokusai_kaibi
body:
A character introduced in [[Toaru Majutsu no Index]], and featured in the sidestory Toaru Majutsu no Index SS: Biohacker Arc.

For a long time only known as the Girl in the Dress (ドレスの少女) or Measure Heart, she is a teenage girl who participates in [[prostitution|compensated dating]] for money. She is an operative of SCHOOL, acquainted with the ways of the Dark Side of Academy City, and the second of the three Gokusai sisters.

She has [[medium hair|medium length]] [[blonde hair|blonde]] [[wavy hair]] styled in a [[ponytail]] and [[brown eyes]]. She usually wears a [[pink dress|pink]] or [[red dress|red]] [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[frilled dress|frilled]] [[dress]], leaving her shoulders [[bare shoulders|bare]] along with [[necklace]]s and [[bracelet]]s and [[white sandals]]. She often has an [[expressionless]] disposition.

She has the ability "Measure Heart (心理定規)" which lets her regulate "the distance between people's hearts," making them feel closer or more distant to a person despite what their memories and reason say otherwise.

title: zorro
body:
A fictional character created in 1919 by American pulp writer Johnston McCulley, appearing in works set in the Pueblo of Los Angeles in Alta California. He is typically portrayed as a dashing masked vigilante who defends the commoners and Indigenous peoples of California against corrupt, tyrannical officials and other villains. His signature all-black costume includes a [[black cape]], a hat known as a sombrero cordobés, and an [[eye mask]] covering the upper half of his face. 

Often considered the original American superhero, his antics would inspire both Superman and Batman.

h4. See also

* [[Zorro (character)]]
* [[The Mask of Zorro]]
* [[The Legend of Zorro]]
* [[Kaiketsu Zorro]]

title: antlers
body:
A pair of branched solid bone horn-like structures that arise from the frontal bone on the head of animals of the deer family, and frequently depicted on [[eastern_dragon|Eastern-style dragons]].  Unlike horns, antlers are branched, quickly develop underneath a covering of furry skin called velvet, consist of dead bone once fully developed, and regularly shed over the course of the animal's life (most commonly every year).

title: lighthouse_(ace_combat)
body:
A [[space elevator|]] featured in [[Ace Combat 7|Ace Combat 7: Skies Unknown]]. Officially known as the [b] International Space Elevator[/b], it was built as a peacekeeping effort on the Usean continent to harness solar energy from the atmosphere to power the globe. 

Its name is the namesake of the main conflict of the game; the Lighthouse War, as the Kingdom of Erusea declared war on Osea over the structure, believing that its real intention was to enforce Osean hegemony on the continent.

title: help:dmail
body:
Dmail is Danbooru's private messaging system, similar in function to e-mail. Its primary use is for exchanging notes between users and delivering account-related notifications.

Your inbox can be accessed through [code]My Account > Messages[/code], or [code]More > Profile > Dmails[/code].

h4. Sending and receiving mail

When you have unread mail in your account, a banner will appear at the top of the page across Danbooru which contains a direct link to your inbox.

To send a dmail to someone, click "New" at the top of the inbox page. Dmails support DText formatting (see [[help:dtext]]).

Dmails can be publicly shared using the "Share" link on the message. Select "Copy link" on it or click it and copy the URL, anyone with that exact link will be able to view the message.

title: kamen_rider_decade
body:
Lead Rider of [[Kamen Rider DCD]], nineteenth show of the Kamen Rider series and tenth of the Heisei generation. The "Destroyer of Worlds".

[[Kadoya Tsukasa]] is an arrogant photographer with no memory of his past, driven to save his own dimension by traveling to 9 other dimensions under the protection of the 9 previous Heisei Riders. Using the [[Decadriver]], he transforms into Kamen Rider Decade.

Decade has a magenta color scheme, and is based on the shield bug [i]graphosoma lineatum[/i] and barcodes. He can transform into the nine previous Heisei Riders, as well as use their abilities via the [[Rider Card]]s. He can also transform into Decade Complete Form, which can conjure "doppelganger" versions of the nine previous Heisei Riders' final forms.

h4. Forms

* [[Kamen Rider decade complete form|Complete Form]]
* [[Kamen Rider decade complete form21|Complete Form21]]

title: suikawari
body:
Suikawari (lit. [i][[watermelon]] splitting[/i]) is a traditional Japanese game which usually takes place at the [[beach]] during the [[summer|summertime]]. It is similar to the Western party game of hitting a piñata: players are given a bat or stick, [[blindfold|blindfolded]] and spun around three times, then attempt to strike the watermelon. Whoever cracks the watermelon first wins and afterwards the remains of the watermelon are shared with all participants of the game.

Might also involve a [[pun]] involving [[Ibuki Suika]] of the Touhou series being hit on the head, somewhat based off a line in Yuyuko in one of the games about going "Suika Bashing" when fighting her.

title: gretsch_6120
body:
Hollow body [[electric guitar]] created and manufactured by American [[instrument]] maker [[Gretsch]] since 1955 in conjuction with Country musician Chet Atkins. This model acquired rapid success in the Rockabilly, Rock n' Roll and Country music scenes, being held by one successful musician to the next, due to this popularity it was then acquired by numerous even-higher profile musicians including [[Eric Clapton]], Pete Townsend of [[The Who]], [[The Beatles]]' [[George Harrison]] and many others, turning it into one of Gretsch's most recognisable models.

Key visual traits of the G6120 include its notably large size compared to more common guitars, four control knobs with one placed at the body's cutaway section, F-holes on its body top and long bridge with either a hard tailpiece of a Bigsby vibrato system.

A vast and wide amount of variations exist of this model to be able to narrow them down to specific versions, from different control configurations and pickups (post #480170) to different fretboard inlays (or no inlays at all), finishes and hardware (post #2323061)

h4. See also
* [[Gretsch White Falcon]]
* [[Gretsch Super Chet]]
* [[Tag Group:Audio Tags]]

title: summer_memories
body:
"Summer Memories":[https://kaguragamesjp.com/product/summer-memories/] is a game developed by "Doujin Otome":[https://kaguragamesjp.com/product-category/kagura-games/dojin-otome/] released in 2020.

The player character reconnects with his extended family during summer break, building bonds and making memories with his two female cousins and aunt. Gameplay involves various mini games that when successfully completed, earns favor with the three women and eventually H-scenes. Progressing with the characters requires the player to meet with them during certain parts of the day assuming certain required conditions are met. There are several side characters with whom the player can do other mini games with to develop favor and in turn view H-scenes with them.

She is the elder sister between the player character's cousins. You build favor with her by helping her with bug-catching for her university assignment.

title: gibson_es-335
body:
Semi-hollow (50% solid-50% hollow) [[electric guitar]], built and manufactured by American [[instrument]] maker [[gibson_brands_inc|Gibson]] since 1958 as part of its ES ([i]Electric Spanish[/i]) series. Largely credited to be the world's first commercialized semi-hollow electric guitar, the ES-335 consists of a solid wood block running through the center of the [[guitar]], with the sides being hollow. It went on to become one of the most popular guitars for genres such as Alternative Rock, Jazz, Blues and R&B among similar others with some of its most famous players being the late B.B. King and [[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]]/Foo Fighters' Dave Grohl.

Visual traits mainly include a round circular double-cutaway body, F-holes, stopbar bridge, four control knobs and the input jack being placed on top of the body.

h4. Examples

* !post #7244507: ES-335, base model
* !post #5868697: ES-345, extra varitone switch
* !post #2490577: ES-355, gold hardware

title: round-headed_mao_die
body:
"圆头耄耋 (yuán tóu mào dié)" is referring to not only a Chinese internet meme, but also a specific orange tabby cat with a round head, and a grumpy or aloof personality. The term "耄耋 (mào dié)" originally refers to elderly people (around 70s or 80s), but in this context, it's a pun for "猫爹 (māo diē)," meaning "cat dad," implying the cat acts like a demanding bad-tempered elder.

[b]Origin of the Cat[/b]

[i]Round-headed Mao Die[/i] originated from a Bilibili user who frequently fed stray cats. One particular round-headed orange cat was noted for its aggressive behavior, driving away other strays. And one day, this cat went into that poor guy's house and he spent several hours to finally let the cat out. That video clip went viral on Chinese social media for this cat's hilarious expression.

That poor guy deleted the original video, but someone did a backup: https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1iXXhYpEcw/

body:

The [[summer uniform|summer version]] of the male uniform has dark blue [[plaid pants]], a [[sweater vest]], and a [[white shirt]] with a [[black necktie]]. The winter uniform has the same pants and brown shoes, but a [[blue jacket|blue]] [[blazer]] and long-sleeved white shirt are worn with it instead underneath a sweater.  World Academy W sweaters are deep blue, tan, white, and brown.

All versions of the World Academy W female uniform have a [[red skirt|red]] [[plaid skirt]] and a white shirt. The uniform is a [[red skirt]] with a dress shirt, tie, and sweater. title: zogok
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series.

[b]MSM-08 Zogok[/b]

[[Zeon]]'s prototype amphibious [[mecha]] ([[mobile suit]]) that was originally intended to appear in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] TV show. Later it appeared in [[Gundam ZZ]] and [[Gundam Unicorn]].

While its gunpla predates the start of Bandai's [[Gundam MSV]] series, it is generally considered to have debuted as part of it, and so on Danbooru that is its base copyright tag.

Zogok's most distinctive weapons are ten "boomerang cutters" mounted in the mecha's head/shoulders.

title: char's_counterattack
body:
Japanese title: 機動戦士ガンダム 逆襲のシャア ([i][b]Kidou Senshi Gundam: Gyakushuu no Char[/b][/i])
English title: [i][b]Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack[/b][/i]

A 1988 anime movie set in the primary U.C. timeline of [[Gundam]], taking place in [b]Universal Century 0093[/b], 5 years after Gundam ZZ.

Making its theatrical debut on March 12, 1988, Char's Counterattack is the final culmination of the original saga begun in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] and continued through [[Zeta Gundam]] and [[Gundam ZZ]], marking the final conflict of the fourteen-year rivalry between [[Amuro Ray]] and [[Char Aznable]], and the end of the [[Earth Federation|EF]]/[[Zeon]] conflicts. Two novels would be written by [[Tomino Yoshiyuki]] based on earlier drafts of the movie, [[Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children|Beltorchika's Children]] and [[Gundam High Streamer|High-Streamer]].

Continued by [[Gundam Unicorn]].

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Char%27s_Counterattack]
other_names: 機動戦士ガンダム逆襲のシャア

Goes by the last name Konstanz and code name "The Valkyrie" in the comic and series, previously going by Valerie Baumer, which only applies to the pilot film's version of her with [[grey skin]]

Has neon [[red hair]], a hairstyle done up in a [[ponytail]], and [[red eyes]]. Any variants of this are considered mostly unrelated to the We Love Cold War series unless specified.

body:

Known in Japanese as 魔神柱 (まじんちゅう, Majin-chuu), where 柱 ([i]chuu[/i], "pillar") is a "Japanese counter word":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_counter_word] for gods, deities and [[spirit tablet]]s.

Best known for an incident described in post #2576688, in which a much-hyped game event quickly ended after the Demon Pillars were quickly defeated due to over-farming by players.

title: ergo_(fate)
body:
Character appearing in [[The Adventures of Lord El-Melloi II]], becoming the temporary student of [[Lord El-Melloi II]]. He has amnesia and forgets previous events as the story continues.

[spoiler]He is a being created years prior as part of the collaborative Ergo experiment, which is where his name comes from. He is the body of [[Iskandar (fate)|]]'s son, Alexander IV, who was given the flesh of three gods to eat, [[Sun Wukong]], [[Set (mythology)|]], and "Oceanus":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oceanus. He was then sent to the bottom of the sea for 2300 years to digest the gods.[/spoiler]

He ends up being the temporary of master of [[Ptolemy (third ascension) (fate)|Ptolemy]] alongside [[Sion Eltnam Sokaris]] for a time.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Sakamoto Mineji]]

A minor character in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s story chapter [i][[se.ra.ph (fate/grand order)|Epic of Remnant: Abyssal Cyber Paradise, SE.RA.PH]][/i]. She is a member of Chaldea's Seraphix branch and one of the few survivors alongside [[Arnold Beckman]] by the time [[Fujimaru Ritsuka]] arrives in the singularity. [spoilers]She is actually [[Sessyoin Kiara]] using Mable's body as a disguise, since the original Mable was already deceased.[/spoilers]

h4. Appearance
* !asset #25932669

h4. See also
* [[Sylvia (fate)|]]

h4. External links
* "Type-Moon Wiki":https://typemoon.fandom.com/wiki/Mable_Macintosh
other_names: マーブル・マッキントッシュ

title: sylvia_(fate)
body:
Member of [[Chaldea Security Organization]], first appearing in the Part 2 prologue (but retroactively appearing in the anime adaptions of [[Babylonia (fate/grand order)|]] and [[Solomon (singularity) (fate/grand order)|Solomon]]). [spoiler]She managed to escape the attack on Chaldea as one of the 11 survivors forming [[Novum Chaldea]]. She has not been seen since, but is presumably one of the off-screen personnel exclusively referred to with their surnames by [[Goredolf Musik]].[/spoiler]

title: pino_(fate)
body:
Minor character in [[Fate/Grand Order]], appearing in [[Kirschtaria Wodime]]'s flashbacks. He is a homeless orphan who ends up rescuing Kirschtaria after an assassination attempt, bringing him back to his shack and protecting him with a magical amulet that allows the user's location to be kept hidden. [spoiler]When he leaves the shack after a few weeks to get more food, he is caught stealing a basket of food and was brutally beaten. While he manages to return with the food to Kirschataria, the beatings combined with malnutrition resulted in his death.[/spoiler]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takenashi Eri]]

h4. Appearance
* !asset #25932559

h4. External links
* "Type-Moon Wiki":https://typemoon.fandom.com/wiki/Pino

title: mnemosyne_(fate)
body:
Character appearing in the [[Lady Reines Case Files]] event of [[Fate/Grand Order]]. [spoiler]She is the personification of a failed computer program designed to confirm [[Fujimaru Ritsuka]]'s existence during rayshifting that was left uncompleted and unused during the events of the first Grand Order. She manifests her grief at being left unused by trapping Ritsuka in a Singularity wherein she tries to alter their memories of [[Leonardo da Vinci (fate)|]], whose appearance she borrows. A fragment of her was later mixed with [[Hephaestion (fate)|]], giving her the true name of [b]Hephaestion Mnemosyne[/b].[/spoiler]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Simosi]]

h4. Appearance
* !asset #25932519

title: minato_aqua_(1st_costume)
body:
The default costume of [[hololive]]'s [[Minato Aqua]]. This costume was designed by [[Topia]].

It consists of a [[maid headdress]] with an [[anchor symbol]], a [[blue dress|blue]] [[frilled dress|frilled]] [[short dress]] with [[puffy short sleeves]] with an [[anchor print]], a [[blue bowtie]], a [[cleavage cutout]], a [[framed breasts|breast frame]] and that is decorated with small [[white bow|white]] [[dress bow|bows]] and a [[large bow|large]] [[back bow]]. She also wears [[wrist cuffs]], frilled [[ankle cuffs]] and [[blue shoes|blue]] [[mary janes]] with [[footwear bow|bows on them]]. 

h4. Other names

Her default costume was given the name [i]Virtual Marine Maid[/i] (バーチャルマリンメイド) in the [i][[Azur Lane]][/i] 2019 collaboration event, since she uses a one-piece swimsuit variant of the default as her main shipgirl costume.

h4. Appearance

* !post #3931939: Profile (2D)
* !post #8056007: Profile (3D)
* !post #5872545: Merchandise
other_names: バーチャルマリンメイド

body:
The 7th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Minato Aqua]].

It's a [[school uniform]] consisting of a [[black choker|black]] [[o-ring choker]] with a [[cat o-ring]], a [[pink scarf]], a [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[white shirt]] with a [[pink bowtie|pink]] [[plaid bowtie]], either a [[black jacket|black]] [[blazer]] or a [[pink sweater]] with a [[high belt]], a [[plaid skirt|plaid]] [[pink skirt|pink]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[miniskirt]] with an [[anchor print]], a [[thigh strap]],  [[white thighhighs|white]] [[cat ear legwear|cat ear thighhighs]] and [[black shoes|black]] [[mary janes]].

Her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this outfit is [[very long hair|very long]] [[parted hair]] with [[side braid]]s that turn into a [[two side up]] with a [[cat hair ornament|cat-shaped]] and [[x hair ornament|x-shaped]] [[hairclip]]s.

title: minato_aqua
body:
A former [[Virtual YouTuber|VTuber]] and member of [[hololive]]'s [[2nd generation (hololive)|]]. A Marine-style [[maid]], turned [[cat girl]]. Designed by [[Gaou (Umaiyo Puyoman)|]].

On August 6, 2024, "she announced":[https://twitter.com/minatoaqua/status/1820781111074803737] that she would be graduating from hololive, with a graduation stream on August 28th.

She has [[purple eyes]] and [[long hair|long]], [[two-tone hair|two-tone]], [[purple hair]] with the [[colored inner hair|inner]] parts being [[blue hair|blue]] and [[streaked hair|streaks]] with [[blunt bangs]], [[sidelocks]] or [[fanged bangs]] and an [[ahoge]], her default hairstyle consists of a pair of [[braid]]s that transition into a pair of [[twin drills|drill-shaped]] [[twintails]] tied with [[blue ribbon|blue]] [[hair ribbon|ribbons]].

title: artemis_(fate)
body:
Archer-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]], along with her bear partner [[orion (bear) (fate)|Orion]]. The depiction of the [[Artemis (mythology)|Greek goddess of the moon and hunting]] of the same name.

Unlike the other divine servants, Artemis manifested in her true form without the need of a vessel body, primarily due to her interference with Orion's saint graph. Because of this, she is summoned as "Orion" while reducing the true Orion into a miniature bear companion. She claimed to do so to "watch over" him.

She first appeared in the event [[Tsuki no Megami wa Odango no Yume wo Miru ka?]] before appearing in the [[Okeanos (fate/grand order)|]] singularity.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[I-IV (longman)|]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Sawashiro Miyuki]]

title: minneapolis_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the heavy cruiser USS [i]Minneapolis[/i] (CA-36). Character designed by [[Mephisto (angraecum)|]], voiced by [[Shimamura Yuu]]. 

She is portrayed as a [[dark-skinned female|dark-skinned]] Native American girl with [[medium breasts]] and [[very long hair|very long]] [[white hair]] in a [[high ponytail]] with [[crossed bangs]] [[hair between eyes|between eyes]]. She has [[facepaint]] underneath her [[red eyes]] and [[bodypaint|on her body]]. 

Her outwear is a [[multicolored cape|multicolored]] [[red cape|red]], [[brown cape|brown]], [[blue cape|blue]], and [[white cape|white]] [[fur-trimmed cape]] with a [[brown hood]] [[hood up|up]]. The rest of her [[revealing clothes|outfit]] is a [[underboob]]-and-[[midriff]]/[[navel]]-exposing  [[breast curtain]], [[fingerless gloves|fingerless]] [[brown gloves]], a [[loincloth]] with a [[brown skirt|brown]] [[showgirl skirt]] held with [[o-ring_bottom|o-rings]], [[highleg panties|highleg]] [[black panties]], and [[red footwear|red]] [[rudder footwear]] over [[ankle wrap]]s.

Her [[rigging]] is the [[huge weapon|huge]] [[cannon]] in the shape of her real-life hull.

title: dingwall_combustion
body:
A line of multiscale [[bass guitar]]s designed and produzed by Canadian Dingwall Guitars. Their main features are fanned frets, two or three slanted pickups and five control knobs arranged in a wide V pattern at the bottom of the body. 

This tag encompasses 4-, [[5-string bass guitar|5-]] and [[6-string bass guitar|6-string]] Dingwall Combustions, Nolly "Getgood" signature Dingwall NGs and other signature or custom shop models sharing the same body and neck geometry and tuner layout.

It's a Black Holy Knight/[[nun|Battle Nun]]-themed outfit, consisting of a [[black veil]], a [[long dress|long]] [[black dress]], a [[guimpe]] with [[breast curtains]], [[puffy long sleeves]] and a [[pelvic curtain]], [[black thighhighs|black]] or [[white thighhighs]] with [[white garter straps]] and [[black shoes|black]] [[strappy heels]]. She has an optional [[black armor|black]] [[black gloves|black]] [[armored dress]] consisting of [[pauldrons]], a [[breastplate]],  [[black gloves|black]] [[gauntlets]], [[greaves]], and black [[sabaton]]s.

title: parrying
body:
The act of blocking an enemy's weapon with your own weapon. Commonly seen in a swordfight, where at least 2 characters with swords or katanas slashing at each other to gain an advantage over the other. Sometimes it's just an improvised blocking or guarding with a weapon (sometimes your own fists).

It can also be seen in [[gameplay mechanics|game mechanics]], where parrying an opponent's attack negates all damage.

title: gibson_thunderbird
body:
A [[bass guitar]] introduced by [[gibson_brands_inc|Gibson]] in 1963. Despite it's lower popularity due to [[fender_musical_instruments_corporation|Fender]]'s dominance in the bass market, the Thunderbird gained a strong following due to it's subjectively more aggressive sound, making it a common sight among heavier genres.

It features a recognizably skewed design only shared by its guitar counterpart [[Gibson Firebird]], both designed by Chrysler's Raymond H. Dietrich along with two large pickups often nicknamed "soapbars".

title: chouginga_gurren-lagann
body:
A [[super robot|giant]] [[mecha]] from [[Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann]], Chouginga Gurren Lagann is [[Lordgenome]]'s battleship Cathedral Terra (renamed Chouginga Dai-Gurren by [[Simon (ttgl)|]]) in humanoid form. The transformation into this form happens when the battleship's core is injected with a great quantity of [[Spiral Power]] by the [[Arc Gurren-Lagann]].

It is the third largest mecha in the series, being almost as large in size as the [[Moon]].

The two drills on its shoulders can be detached and combined to form a single drill, then used to perform the [i]Chouginga Giga Drill Breaker[/i] attack. According to Lordgenome, its power equals that of a sub-universe.

title: gurren-lagann
body:
When Simon's [[Lagann]] mecha and Kamina's [[Gurren]] mecha combine by way of Lagaan drilling into Gurren's head, they form the titular Gunman of the [[Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann]] series, known as [[Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann]].

Separated, neither Gunmen are particularly noteworthy or powerful, but together, their power rises drastically and they gain the ability to produce an endless amount of drills in different sizes. title: mitsugashira_enoko
body: Cerberus of Forested Silence First appeared in [[Touhou]] 19: [[Unfinished Dream of All Living Ghost]] as a boss and playable character. Enoko is an immortal yamainu with [[dog ears]] and [[multiple tails|three]] [[dog tail|tails]]. Her hair comes in [[two-tone hair|two tones]], [[purple hair|purple]] and [[white hair|white]]/[[grey hair|light grey]]. Notably, she has two [[bear trap]]s, one on each arm, which opens and closes depending on her hand movements. Enoko works for the Keiga Family as part of their operations to take over the surface world. In reality, as with [[Son Biten]] and [[Tenkajin Chiyari]], she is a spy whose true allegiance lies with [[Nippaku Zanmu]]. She was tasked with sabotaging the Keiga Family's invasion plans from within by playing them for time as part of Zanmu's gambit to prevent a surface war. At some time in the past, prior to her acquiring a [[personification|humanoid]] form, Enoko saw a [[aged down|young]] [[Kirisame Marisa]] when she first ran away from home into the [[Forest of Magic]]. h4. See also * [[Mitsugashira Enoko (Dog)]] * "Honey Trap":[/pools/2486] h4. External Links * "Touhou Wiki: Mitsugashira Enoko":https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Enoko_Mitsugashira

The design of this outfit is identical to the swimsuit Leo wore in [[Fire Emblem Fates]]’ "Beach Brawl":[https://fireemblem.fandom.com/wiki/Beach_Brawl] DLC. The Lilith-shaped floatie is also from that DLC.

Note that it's possible (especially for older artwork), to depict Leo in a swimsuit without it being the one described above, in which case this tag should not be used.

title: veggietales
body:
A CG animated series about fruit and vegetable characters. Since it first aired in 1993, it was one of many animated shows to use 3D animation when other animated shows at the time still use 2D animation. title: idolmaster
body:
Idolmaster (アイドルマスター, stylized as [i]iDOLM@STER [/i]) is a 2005 video game series by [[Namco]] (later [[Bandai Namco]]), originally released for the arcade and subsequently for multiple platforms including Xbox 360, PlayStation Portable, Nintendo DS, PS3, PS4, PS5, and PC. The game follows the career of a producer from the 765 Production studio handling ten young [[idol]]s.

Eventually adapted into mutliple manga, a 2007 mecha re-imagining by [[Sunrise (company)|]], [[Idolmaster Xenoglossia]], and a more faithful 2011 anime which precedes the events of [[Idolmaster 2]]. The series has also spawned four mobile game spinoffs that focus on new groups of idols ([[Idolmaster Cinderella Girls]], [[Idolmaster Million Live!]], [[Idolmaster Side-M]], and [[Gakuen Idolmaster]]), as well as spinoffs featuring all branches, such as [[Idolmaster Poplinks]]. It has also spawned a HTML5 platform game spinoff, [[Idolmaster Shiny Colors]], as well as a non-game VTuber spinoff in [[Idolmaster va-liv]].

title: bang_dream!_it's_mygo!!!!!
body:
BanG Dream! It's MyGO!!!!! is an anime in the [[BanG Dream!]] franchise. It aired from June 29, 2023 until September 14, 2023, with a second part titled BanG Dream! Ave Mujica airing from January 2, 2025 until March 27, 2025. After the final episode, a new season was announced.

The series also includes two comics:
* [i]BanG Dream! It's MyGO!!!!! Ame ni Soyoide Hare o Kou[/i], Illustrated by [[Yuama]] with screenplay by "Haibuti Yotsuzi":https://twitter.com/haibuti_yotsuzi. Started serialization on December 27, 2024.
* [i]BanG Dream! Ave Mujica -manuscriptus-[/i] by [[Hiroyama Pinfu]]. Started serialization on January 10, 2025.

In addition to the series having similar themes, on 2024-07-05, a joint live concert between [[MyGO!!!!! (bang dream!)|]] and [[Girls Band Cry]]'s [[Togenashi Togeari]] on 2025-01-12 "was":[https://twitter.com/bang_dream_info/status/1809067177053728832] "announced":[https://twitter.com/girlsbandcry/status/1809067702126063829], prompting a lot of [[crossover]] fanart.

title: bootleg_metal_sonic_plush
body:
A [[character doll|plush]] of [[Metal Sonic]] from the [[Sonic (series)|Sonic the Hedgehog series]] famous (infamous?) for its exaggerated, off-model features. It sports very long shoes, short limbs, a disproportionately [[long nose|long]] and [[pointy nose]], and quills that appear uneven or almost pyramid-like. Its eyes are notably elongated and squished, giving Metal Sonic an expression that many describe as [[unamused]] or oddly quirky.

Despite—or because of—its unusual appearance, the Bootleg Metal Sonic Plush has become a cult favorite within the Sonic the Hedgehog community. Videos on platforms like YouTube have associated the “hue hue hue” audio (an isolated part of [[Sonic CD]]'s JP [[Stardust Speedway]] Bad Future music track) with the plush, further elevating its status among fans and collectors. This [[meme]] originated around 2021 and gained wider attention by 2024, when content creators used clips of the plush paired with quirky audio to humorous effect, also coinciding with the character's appearance during the [[Sonic the Hedgehog 3 (movie)|]] film's post-credits sequence.

h4. External links

* "Know Your Meme":https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/bootleg-metal-sonic-plush-hue-hue-hue

title: ichinose_suzuka
body:
A character in [[DraPri Guu-ta-life]] & [[DraPri Guu-ta-life 2]]. A childhood friend of [[Miyamoto Takeru]] & daughter of [[Ichinose Akino]].

She has [[blue eyes]], [[large breasts]], and [[medium hair|medium length]] [[brown hair]] stylized in [[bangs]], [[hair between eyes]], and a [[side ponytail]] held by a [[blue scrunchie|blue]] [[hair scrunchie|hair]] [[scrunchie]], [[hairclip]], and [[hair ornament]].

She usually wears a [[off shoulder]] [[off-shoulder sweater|sweat]][[sweater|er]], [[criss-cross halter|criss-cross]] [[halterneck]], a [[frilled skirt|frilled]] [[black skirt|black]] [[miniskirt|mini]][[skirt]], and [[white boots|white]] [[knee boots]].

In her [[dragon girl]] form she has [[dragon horns]], [[orange wings|orange]] [[dragon wings]], and a [[dragon tail]].

title: yuzuriha_ringo
body:
A character introduced in [[Toaru Kagaku no Dark Matter]].

Yuzuriha seems to possess a very cold, melancholic and quiet disposition as seen where she nonchalantly ignored a group of delinquent thugs threatening her and attempting to kidnap and sell her to a research facility and when [[Kakine Teitoku]] bursted in and brutalized the thugs, Yuzuriha again did not displayed any strong emotion to his brutality and instead agreed to come with him without question despite the obvious suspicious circumstances surrounding the situation.

She has [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]] styled in a [[bob cut]] with [[bangs]], [[black eyes]], and typically wears a [[pink dress|pink]] [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[sundress|sun]][[dress]] with black [[spaghetti straps]] under a [[green coat|green]] [[coat]] (often [[open coat|open]] and [[off shoulder|off her shoulders]]) and [[white boots]].  Her face is usually depicted as [[expressionless]].

title: cyrille_(shining_force_exa)
body:
The secondary main protagonist of [[Shining Force EXA]]. Her name in English is Cyrille.

Cyril has [[long hair|long]], [[blonde hair]] in a [[half updo]] held up with a downward facing [[black bow]]. She has [[blue eyes]], and is often seen with a long tunic with black inlay with a [[mandarin collar]]. She is often seen with a [[book]] covered in small gold chain, with some of them enwrapping Cyril herself. She also wears a [[black leotard]] and [[white boots|white]] [[knee boots]].

Her personality has been listed as 'strange', and likes to shut people out and be alone. She's typically seen with [[Zhirra]], a small animal that she has what Cyril calls a 'friend' and not a pet.

body:

Seat 8 in [[Negi Springfield]]'s class. She is an orphan with a determined personality. It is well known that she has a crush on her teacher [[Takahata T Takamichi]].

She can be quite stubborn and give into violent outbursts, but also has a fierce protective nature. This greatly shows when she's with [[Yukihiro Ayaka]] and Negi. For her [[Pactio]], she can summon either a [[harisen]] or [[ensis exorcizans|her huge sword]].

She has [[very long hair|very long]] [[orange hair|orange]] [[twintails]] and [[heterochromia|heterochromatic]] eyes; her left is dark blue and her right is light green.

She is "Baka Red" in the [[Mahora Baka Rangers]] study group.

A white ball with an [[^_^]] expression, Lamy's signature [[heart ahoge]] and [[bowtie]] and the text "[i]やめなー[/i] "([i]yamenaa[/i], meaning "stop it" or "cut it out"), a catchphrase associated with Lamy and often thrown at Nene's for her rather immature (and quite inappropriate for an idol) sense of humor. It's sometimes drawn with Polka's arms.

title: akemi_(blue_archive)
body:
A non-playable character from [[Blue Archive]]. 

Ex-Leader of the Sukebans, and one of the Seven Prisoners. Known as "The Legendary Sukeban".
The academy she hails from is unknown, but there was a specific incident where numerous vehicles were destroyed and several students injured by her and her alone.

Her full name is Kurihama Akemi.

She has a tall, [[muscular female|muscular]] figure with [[long hair|long]], [[blonde hair|blonde]], [[wavy hair]] resting [[hair over shoulder|over her shoulder]].

Her attire is a parody of [[Geese Howard]] from [[Fatal Fury]].
She wears a [[sarashi]] that covers her [[medium breasts]], [[fingerless gloves|fingerless]] [[red gloves]], a [[studded belt]], the bottom half of a [[red serafuku]], and [[high heels]].

The three lines of text on her skirt are translated as:
* First line: "[i]The bloodthirsty old woman said she's the upper demon of the sand.[/i]"
* 2nd line: "[i]To be invincible in this world, one must heed the old woman’s words.[/i]"
* 3rd line:  "[i]I defy death and conquer fire, my power is overwhelming.[/i]"

But it can also be read as:
* First line: "[i]The very best young lady.[/i]"
* 2nd line: "[i]The invincible sukeban.[/i]"
* 3rd line:  "[i]I'm cute.[/i]"

Her weapons of choice are a [[Browning M2]] [[heavy machine gun]] and an [[M202 FLASH]] [[rocket launcher]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #7919987: Profile

title: new_jersey_(belated_battleships)
body:
The personification of [[USS New Jersey (BB-62)]] as depicted in the [[Kantai Collection]] fanfiction Belated Battleships by TheJMPer.

She has [[blonde hair]] worn in a [[braid]] and [[blue eyes]]. She is huge at over six feet tall and visibly muscular. Although her chest is not small by any means, it is shown in-story that she has [[breast envy]] with regards to [[Musashi (kancolle)|]] and other even bustier ship girls. There is a [[scar]] across her stomach. Clothing-wise, she wears a blue top with elbow-length sleeves with "Navy" embroidered in gold, a [[blue vest]], [[blue shorts]] with gold trim, [[blue shoes]] and three watches on her left wrist. Underneath, she wears a gold sports bra and red "undershorts". She sometimes wears a gold [[scarf]] and oversized aviator [[sunglasses]].

Although not explicitly stated as such, lacking official art, quite a bit of fanart abbreviates the shorts into [[buruma]] and gives her [[white thighhighs]] with [[garter straps]] that seem to be appropriated from her [[Pacific (kancolle)|]] counterpart.

h4. See also

* [[New Jersey (pacific)|The older Pacific depiction of New Jersey]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: USS New Jersey (BB-62)":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USS_New_Jersey_(BB-62)]

title: lee-enfield
body:
The Lee-Enfield is a series of [[bolt action]] [[rifle]]s that came in several models, chambered for .303 British [[rifle cartridge|cartridge]]. The [[weapon]] was named after its designer, James Paris [b]Lee[/b]—and the rifling design location—the Royal Small Arms Factory in [b]Enfield[/b]. It was the standard rifle of [[united kingdom|British]] and Commonwealth [[military|forces]] during [[World War I]] and [[World War II]]. 

The feed system is detachable 10-[[ammunition|round]] [[magazine (weapon)|magazine]], usually fed from 5-round [[clip (weapon)|clips]].

* !post #6225815: Full-length Lee-Enfield (top) and the No. 5 Mk I "Jungle Carbine" variant with shortened stock (center), on top of the FN Fal. 

h4. See also
* [[Lee-Enfield (Girls' Frontline)]]
* [[List of Weapons]]

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Lee-Enfield":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lee–Enfield

title: mauser_98
body:
A series of [[bolt action]] [[rifle]]s designed and manufactured by Mauser, chambered for 7.92×57mm and utilizing a 5-round internal magazine. The Mauser 98 is recognizable by its two handguard metal bands on the front (one serves for sling swivels), ability to store a [[cleaning rod]] inside the lower handguard, exposed barrel, and semi-grip buttstock.

This tag includes any variants, such as:

* [b]Gewehr 98[/b], introduced in 1898. The original model that served the German military during [[World War I]]. Has a straight bolt handle.
* [b]Karabiner 98k[/b], introduced in 1935. Essentially the shortened Gewehr 98 of it with a bent bolt. Used by the Germans during [[World War II]]. Generally known as "Kar 98" (with or without space) for short.
* Other foreign-produced copies such as the Polish Wz.29 and Chinese "Type 24":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chiang_Kai-shek_rifle].

h4. See also

* [[Gewehr 41]]
* [[Kar98k (Girls' Frontline)]]
* [[List of Weapons]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Gewehr 98":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gewehr_98
* "Wikipedia: Karabiner 98 kurz":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karabiner_98k

It consists of a [[blue apron]] with a black-trimmed [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[white shirt]] and a [[black bowtie|black]] [[striped bowtie]].

This is the default outfit for [[Sora (blue archive)|]], who works here. title: mdr_(girls'_frontline)
body:
A T-Doll (android) that is armed with (and thus representing) the [[Desert Tech MDR]], the "Micro Dynamic Rifle", in [[Girls' Frontline]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] with a [[one side up]], atop which she wears a [[beret]]. MDR has [[heterochromia]]. Like most T-Doll characters, she is seen wearing [[tactical clothes]], paired with a [[backpack]]. She also wears [[gloves]] and [[black pantyhose]].

Her official artwork shows her carrying a [[flip phone|mobile phone]], and she's often characterized as a massive shitposter with an online following. In the prequel spin-off game, [[Girls' Frontline Neural Cloud|Neural Cloud]], MDR appears as [[Kuro (neural cloud)|]].

title: ryuu_ga_gotoku_(series)
body:
Series of open-world action games developed by Ryuu Ga Gotoku Studio and published by [[Sega]]. Originally known outside of Japan as the [b]Yakuza[/b] series, before switching to [b]Like a Dragon[/b] after the 7th mainline game.

The series is famous for the contrast between the serious main stories and comical side stories, numerous minigames, as well as tie-in with several [[real life]] Japanese brands.

title: gardening_shears
body:
A variety of [[shears]], effectively a heavier duty [[scissors]], used in gardening and agriculture.

h4. Types

* [b]Pruning shears[/b]: Small shears similar to household scissors used for pruning small branches from plants.  Also known as [i]secateurs[/i] in UK English.
** Straight blade: Pruning shears with straight blades, nearly identical to household scissors. Ex: post #6087615.
*** Anvil pruners: Pruners where it features a single cutting blade that meets up with a widen flat end when cutting.
** Curved blade: Pruning shears with a curved blade.
*** Bypass pruners: Pruners where one blade is convex and the other blade is concave, used to better hold branches. Ex: post #5969022.
*** Parrot-beak pruners: Pruners where both blades are concave to better hold branches as they're cutting.
* [b]Loppers[/b]: A larger long-handled two-handed version of pruning shears.  Used for cutting branches that pruning shears can't handle. Features the same different blade types as pruning shears. ex: post #5038306.
* [b]Hedging shears[/b]: Large long-handled two-handed shears featuring long blades for trimming hedges and shrubs.  Also known as a manual hedge trimmers, but due to the commonality of motorized hedge trimmers they're frequently branded as hedging shears to better differentiate them. Ex: post #1705185.

h4. See also

* [[Hedge trimmer]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Pruning shears":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pruning_shears]
* "Wikipedia: Loppers":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loppers]
* "Wikipedia: Hedge trimmer":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hedge_trimmer]

[b]TRB[/b] and [b]TRBX[/b] are a series of [[bass_guitar|bass guitars]] designed and produced by [[Yamaha]]. [b]TRB[/b] originally launched in the early 90s as a versatile 6-string model but later has expanded into a full range of 5-string and 4-string models, while [b]TRBX[/b] lineup features the same body geometry and a slightly shorter 34" scale length and serves as a replacement for now discontinued [b]RBX[/b] and [b]TRB[/b] series. 

For convenience's sake this tag acts as an umbrella tag for both TRB/TRBX and RBX lines of bass guitars due to their visual similarity.

title: illuminate_(helldivers)
body:
[b]The Illuminate[/b] are one of the many enemy factions in the [[Helldivers (series)|]] games. 

In the first game, they were introduced as an advanced Alien race with an enlightened society they favor intelligence and the use of nano machines. Despite the Illuminate trying to have peaceful relationships with Super Earth, the Super Earth government instead launched an unprovoked attack on the Illuminates on the false narrative that the Aliens were secretly hiding weapons of mass destruction to secretly attack Super Earth, forcing the Illuminate to defend themselves.

The Illuminate returns in Helldivers 2 where it was revealed that after Super Earth conquered their homeworld, the aliens were forced to not only give up their technology to the humans but were forced into exile where many of their race were genocide by Super Earth despite promises of safe passage. Angered and wanting revenge for what Super Earth did to their race, The Illuminate returns during the later stages of the 2nd Galactic War with their new mind control powers where they capture Super Earth citizens and turned them into mindless zombies called "Voteless". While they initially attack Super Earth colonies with large cities, during the "Heart of Democracy" event The Illuminate launches a surprise attack that catches the humans off guard and invade Super Earth itself.

title: chokha
body:
A type of overcoat that is part of the traditional clothing of people from the Caucasus, such as Georgians, Circassians, and Chechens, among others, as well as other groups that have interacted with them, like Russian Cossacks.

They are most recognizable from the attached [[gazyr|gazyrs]] - several fabric tubes lined up side-by-side in a row on the breast, formerly used to hold rifle charges, but now mainly decorative. Chokhas also characteristically have a v-shaped or triangular neckline that is often very deep, in many cases extending down to the breasts, exposing the wearer's shirt (usually [[dress shirt|button-up]]) underneath. The bottom hem of a chokha is generally pleated and extends down far enough to cover the knees, but not touch the ground. They may be any color, but are prototypically black or some other dark color.

title: whip_scorpion
body:
A group of arachnids belonging to the order of Uropygi.  They possess [[scorpion]]-like pincers, a long whip-like tail, eight legs; six legs for walking and their front most two legs for feelers.  They do no possess venom glands, but do have glands near the rear of their abdomen that produce a combination of acids which they can spray when they're bothered.

Their naming comes from their similarity to true scorpions, but they're more closely related to [[spider]]s.

h4. External link

* "Wikipedia: Uropygi":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uropygi]

title: harvestmen
body:
[[Arachnid]]s from the order Opiliones.  Also known as harvesters, harvest spiders, or daddy longlegs.  They're particularly remembered for their many species that possess very long slender legs.  A harvestmen's body appears as a single oval-shape and they have a single pair of eyes. Spiders in comparison have a clear separation of their two body parts and possess 3-4 pairs of eyes.  Harvestmen feed on small insects and plant matter, and can consume solid food.  This is unlike spiders which can only consume liquid food.

Urban legend has that harvestmen possess extremely deadly poison, but have fangs to short to penetrate human skin.  Despite this claim, no known harvestmen species possesses venom and all lack the fangs necessary to inject venom.  Instead of fangs they possess tiny little gripper claws, that are too small to penetrate human skin.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Opiliones":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opiliones]

title: picture_hat
body:
A picture hat is an elaborate woman's [[hat]] with a wide brim, worn with [[gown]] or in [[formal clothes]] settings. They resemble [[sun hat]] and are often heavily decorated with [[hat flower]], [[hat feather]] or other [[hat ornament]]. This style of hat was featured in virtually every decade of the 20th century and has a history dating back to at least the 18th century, as shown in pictures by 18th-century English painters such as Reynolds and Gainsborough.

h4. See also
* [[fascinator]]
* [[pillbox hat]]
* [[Tag Group:Headwear]]

title: strangling
body:
Squeezing or holding a person's neck to restrict their breathing. May be used as an attack to render someone unconscious, or as part of [[rough sex]] or [[BDSM]] play.

If the person is completely unable to breathe, then it's also [[asphyxiation]].

The less violent form of this is [[hands on another's neck]].

Not to be confused with [[choking on object]].

h4. See also

* [[asphyxiation]]
* [[choke hold]]
* [[chokeposting (meme)]]
* [[hands on another's neck]]
* [[neck lift]]
* [[scissorhold]]

title: choke_hold
body:
A [b]choke hold[/b], or stranglehold, is any type of unarmed strangulation technique used to submit an opponent or incapacitate a foe by restricting their airway (choking) or blood flow (strangulation). Choke holds are common in [[martial arts|]] such as [[judo]], Brazilian jiu-jitsu and sambo.

In judo these are known as shime-waza, and were originally codified by Kano Jigoro and the Kodokan judo school.

For Danbooru purposes, choke holds are to be tagged [[strangling]], not [[choking on object]].

h4. Common types of choke holds
* [[triangle choke]]
* [[rear naked choke]]
* [[arm triangle choke]]
* [[gogoplata]]

h4. See also

* [[asphyxiation]]
* [[battle]]
* [[fighting]]
* [[full nelson]]: another way to restrain someone’s head using arms
* [[scissorhold]]: restraining someone’s head using legs
* [[strangling]]
* [[struggling]]
* [[wrestling]]

h4. External links
* "Choke hold on Wikipedia":[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Chokehold]

title: fast_&_furious
body:
A [[car]]-focused American action movie series that heavily features street racing, chase scenes, and vehicular action sequences. The series notoriously gets more and more ridiculous with each entry, moving further away from the grounded street racing featured in earlier films to heist and espionage plots with over-the-top stunts that usually involve [[sports car]]s performing physically impossible feats.

Known as the [b]Wild Speed[/b] series in Japan.

title: rukuriri_(girls_und_panzer)
body:
A character from the series [[Girls und Panzer]].

Tank commander of a [[Matilda (tank)|Matilda]] on the "St. Gloriana":[#dtext-see-also] tankery team.

Her nickname is a type of tea from Kenya.

Initially an unnamed mob character with several nicknames, she was eventually given the official name Rukuriri. At first she was given the fan nickname Ushiroda ([tn]Ushiro=Behind, Da=Common Last Name Ending[/tn]) due to the scene (Episode 4, ~10:15-10:45) where she thinks Team Duck was hiding in a garage in front of her, only for them to appear behind her from the floor. When she realizes this, she shouts "後ろだ (Ushiro da)", which means "They're behind us", which also provided the genesis for her fan name.

Voiced by [[Kurata Masayo]] "[1]":[#dtext-external-links].

[expand=Official Character Bio]

h5. St. Gloriana Girls College

h6. Original Anime

Tank commander of a Matilda. In a school styled with elegance she has an unusually hot-blooded nature, and her tone of voice is also rude. Supports the front lines with a high degree of competency.

[tn]Source: "[2]":[#dtext-external-links][/tn]

h6. Das Finale

[i]Same as [b]Original Anime[/b].[/i]

[tn]Source: "[3]":[#dtext-external-links][/tn]

[/expand]

title: nightingale_(gundam)
body:
From [[Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children|Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children]], the [[Neo Zeon]] [[nightingale (gundam)|MSN-04II Nightingale]] is the alternate interpretation of the [[Sazabi|MSN-04 Sazabi]] and the personal [[mecha|mobile suit]] of [[Char Aznable]] in the novel. Together with [[Amuro Ray]]'s [[Hi-Nu Gundam|RX-93-ν2 Hi-Nu Gundam]], the Nightingale was one of the most advanced mobile suits of its time in U.C. 0093. Both mobile suits are equipped with the revolutionary [[Psycho Frame]] technology. Its mechanical designer in real life is [[Izubuchi Yutaka]].

In many ways the Nightingale can be considered as the "big brother" of the Sazabi, and although it is a Mobile Suit, its specifications are comparable to that of a Mobile Armor customized for a Newtype. Aside from its bigger size, this psycho frame-equipped MS also featured more weapons, including 10 [[funnels (gundam)|]], a mega [[beam rifle]], a pair of vulcan cannons, a [[beam cannon]], two [[energy sword|beam sabers]] and a [[shield]] which carries a beam tomahawk and several micro missiles. The Nightingale also has a pair of [[extra arms|hidden arms]] mounted behind the front skirt armor, a pair of back-mounted vernier binders to ensure high mobility for the large mobile suit, and five propellant tanks (three on the backpack and two underneath the rear skirt armor) to fuel its large number of thrusters. 

h4.See also

* [[Hi-Nu Gundam]]
* [[Sazabi]]

title: re-gz_custom
body:
A fictional variable geometry manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in [[Gundam MSV]].

[b]RGZ-91B Re-GZ Custom[/b]

Customized and fully-transformable version of the Re-GZ, where the Back Weapon System's weapons are strengthened as it is integrated into the [[Mobile Suit]], improving its combat performance and allowing it to transform into Wave Rider mode at will. This MS by [[Anaheim Electronics]] was originally developed for [[Amuro Ray]] (who previously used the [[Re-GZ]]), but deployment of the more advanced [[Nu Gundam]] meant this mecha was never used by him.

The most notable feature of this version is its [[beam_rifle|beam assault rifle]], which looks a lot like the [[ak-47|Kalashnikov]] series of assault rifles.

Designed by [[Akitaka Mika]].

title: setsubun
body:
[b]Setsubun[/b] (節分, lit. "seasonal division") is the last day of winter in the Japanese calendar. It usually corresponds to February 3rd in the Gregorian calendar.

A ritual performed on this day is to throw roasted soybeans in order to drive away [[oni]]; this is known as [[mamemaki]].

In the Kansai region, it's customary to eat [[makizushi]] while facing this year's lucky direction; this practice is known as [[ehoumaki]].

h4. See also

* [[mamemaki]]

title: eggette
body:
A [i][[Sonic (series)|]][/i] [[original]] fan character based off of [[Dr. Eggman]] as he appears in [i][[Sonic Mania]][/i]. Also sometimes called Omelette or Eggatha.

In Flying Battery Zone Act 2, Eggman fights the player in a spider [[mecha]] internally referred to as the "Spider Mobile". The original sprite she derived from simply had Eggman hanging upside down in the mecha. The trend only really began to take off due to "an interpretation":https://twitter.com/blackbookalpha/status/901971073096335360 by [[Alpha Gamboa]]; due to the fact that his visible face looked like that of a young girl in that state, the user had drawn the "head" of that sprite as a young girl with Eggman's trademarked glasses and a tiara reinterpreted from Eggman's nose, and her costume directly inspired from the Spider Mobile's design. From that point on, fans began to draw the character closely resembling that original version.

* !asset #25911346: Alpha's interpretation

In most versions she's portrayed as an entity akin to [[Bowser Jr.]]: a bratty younger version of her "parent". However, whether she's actually related to Eggman or not is usually up for interpretation; in some she's blood by cloning, by her being a niece, or some coupling, and in others she's an [[android]] powered by a jewel on her head. In any case, she is just as technologically proficient as her originator and antagonizes [[Sonic the Hedgehog]] as well.

Do not mistake her for a younger genderswap of Dr. Eggman (see [[Eggma'am]] for a genderswap instead), nor a transformation in the vein of [[Super Crown]] fan characters (which often use the "-ette" suffix in English).
h4. See also
* [[Belle the Tinkerer]]
* [[Hope Kintobor]]
* [[Sage (sonic)|]]

h4. External Links
* "Spider Mobile used as inspiration":[https://sonic.fandom.com/wiki/Spider_Mobile]
* "Original Post by Alpha Gamboa":[https://twitter.com/blackbookalpha/status/901971073096335360]
* "Eggette/Omelette | Know Your Meme":[https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/eggette-omelette]

title: sonic_the_hedgehog_(movie)
body:
A 2020 action-adventure comedy film based on the [[Sonic (series)|]] video game franchise, directed by Jeff Fowler and written by Pat Casey and Josh Miller and produced by [[Paramount Pictures]].

The film had a great controversy over Sonic's initial [[ugly sonic|humanoid looking design]], which has also been described as adjacent to the uncanny valley. Due to the overwhelmingly bad reception to this design, the movie was postponed and Sonic got a redesign much closer to his game counterpart, which received much more praise.

The film stars Ben Schwartz as the voice for [[Sonic the Hedgehog]] and [[Jim Carrey]] as [[Dr. Eggman|Dr. Robotnik]], as well as James Marsden, Tika Sumpter, Natasha Rothwell, Adam Pally, and Neal McDonough. In the film, Sonic teams up with local town sheriff [[Tom Wachowski]] to find his lost rings while they escape from Robotnik.

h4. See also

* [[Ugly Sonic]] - The aforementioned earlier, unpopular design.

title: crow
body:
A large, all-black passerine [[bird]].

Scientifically, crows are one species of bird in the broader Corvidae family, which includes crows, ravens, rooks, jackdaws, jays, magpies, treepies, choughs, and nutcrackers. On Danbooru, "crow" includes all visually-similar birds in the Corvidae family.

Birds in the Corvidae family range in size from the relatively small pigeon-size jackdaws (Eurasian and Daurian) to the Common Raven of the Holarctic region and Thick-billed Raven of the highlands of Ethiopia. The 40 or so members of Corvus genus occur on all temperate continents (except South America) and several offshore and oceanic islands.

Crow species found in Japan, aside from [[magpie]]s, jays and nutcrackers, include the rook, [[carrion crow]], Eurasian & Daurian jackdaws, the large-billed crow, and the common raven.

[[Touhou]] characters [[Shameimaru Aya]] and [[Himekaidou Hatate]] are crow [[tengu]], while [[Reiuji Utsuho]] is a hell raven youkai.

h4. See also

h1. Notable Roles

title: the_crow_(comic)
body:
[b]The Crow[/b] is a supernatural superhero [[comic]] book series created by [[united states|American]] comic writer and artist "James O'Barr":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_O'Barr revolving around the titular character of the same name. 

The series, which was originally created by O'Barr as a means of dealing with the death of his fiancée at the hands of a drunk driver, was first published by "Caliber Comics":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caliber_Comics in 1989. 

It became an underground success, and was later adapted into [[the crow (movie)|a film of the same name]] in 1994. Three film sequels, a television series, and numerous books and comic books (published by numerous companies) have also been subsequently produced.

The Crow has been translated into almost a dozen languages and has sold around 750,000 copies worldwide.

title: the_bad_guys_(movie)
body: A 3D animated film developed by [[Dreamworks|DreamWorks Animation]] and released in 2022, based on an Australian series of children's books. The film focuses on a gang of criminal anthropomorphic animals who, after being caught during a heist, attempt to feign reformation to avoid a jail sentence. It is strongly influenced by heist genre films with a 2D-3D visual style inspired by French and Japanese animation, including [[Toriyama Akira|Akira Toriyama]] and [[Lupin III]].

title: sonic_the_hedgehog_1
body:
[b]Sonic the Hedgehog[/b] is a platform [[video game]] developed by Sonic Team and published by [[SEGA]] for the [[Sega Mega Drive]]/Sega Genesis [[game console]].  It is the first game in the [[Sonic (series)|Sonic franchise]]. It was released in North America in June 1991 and in PAL regions and Japan the following month. 

The game features [[Sonic the Hedgehog]], who can run at supersonic speeds, setting out on a quest to defeat [[Dr. Eggman]] (Robotnik), a scientist who has imprisoned animals inside hostile [[robot]]s and seeks the powerful [[Chaos Emerald]]s. 

The gameplay involves collecting [[ring (sonic)|]]s as a form of health, and a simple control scheme, with jumping and attacking controlled by a single button.

Development began in 1990 when Sega ordered its developers to create a game featuring a new mascot for the company. After considering a number of suggestions, the developers decided on a blue hedgehog and named themselves "Sonic Team" to match their character. Sonic the Hedgehog, designed for fast gameplay, was influenced by games by [[Mario (series)|Super Mario]] series creator Miyamoto Shigeru. 

Sonic the Hedgehog uses a novel technique that allows Sonic's sprite to roll along curved scenery, which originated in a tech demo created by programmer Naka Yuji. The music was composed by Nakamura Masato, songwriter of the J-pop band [i]Dreams Come True[/i].

Sonic the Hedgehog was well received by critics, who praised its visuals, audio, and gameplay. It is widely considered one of the greatest video games of all time. It was also commercially successful, becoming one of the best-selling video games of all time with approximately 24 million copies sold worldwide across all platforms. Furthermore, it established the Genesis as a key player in the 16-bit era and allowing it to compete with Nintendo's [[Super Nintendo]] Entertainment System console. 

The game has been ported a number of times, and inspired several clones, a successful franchise, and adaptations into [[sonic the hedgehog (movie)|other media]]. It was followed by [[Sonic the Hedgehog 2]] in 1992.

title: ugly_sonic
body:

Particular attention has been called to the design's human-like teeth.

The name "Ugly Sonic" was given in the 2022 [i][[Chip 'N Dale Rescue Rangers (movie)|]][/i] film, where the design was made into an actual character voiced by comedian Tim Robinson.

title: emma_stone
body: Emily Jean "Emma" Stone (born November 6, 1988) is an American actress and producer. Her accolades include two Academy Awards, two British Academy Film Awards, and two Golden Globe Awards. In 2017, she was the world's highest-paid actress and named by Time magazine as one of the 100 most influential people in the world.Stone began acting as a child in a theater production of The Wind in the Willows in 2000. As a teenager, she relocated to Los Angeles and made her television debut in In Search of the New Partridge Family (2004), a reality show that produced only an unsold pilot. After small television roles, she appeared in a series of well-received teen comedy films, such as [[Superbad (movie)|]] (2007), Zombieland (2009), and Easy A (2010), which was Stone's first leading role. Following this breakthrough, she starred in the romantic comedy Crazy, Stupid, Love (2011) and the period drama The Help (2011), and gained wider recognition as [[Gwen Stacy]] in the 2012 superhero film [[The Amazing Spider-Man]] and its [[the Amazing Spider-Man 2|2014 sequel]].  Stone received nominations for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for playing a recovering drug addict in Birdman (2014) and Abigail Masham in The Favourite (2018). The latter marked her first of many collaborations with director Yorgos Lanthimos. She won two Academy Awards for Best Actress for her roles as an aspiring actress in the romantic musical [[La La Land]] (2016) and a resurrected suicide victim in Lanthimos' comic fantasy [[Poor Things (movie)|]] (2023). She also portrayed tennis player Billie Jean King in Battle of the Sexes (2017) and the title role in Cruella (2021). On television, she starred in the dark comedy miniseries Maniac (2018) and The Curse (2023).

title: orphan_(movie)
body:
Orphan is a 2009 psychological, slasher movie directed by Jaume Collet-Serra. The movie follows the Coleman family, who adopts an orphan girl named [[Esther (orphan)|]] after the family suffers a personal tragedy after their third child's miscarriage. While the family at first gets along with their new daughter with Esther being friends with their first two children, the Colemans soon start to realize something wrong with Esther and Esther has a dark secret and her own motives for the family.

A prequel, [b]Orphan: First Kill[/b] was released in 2022 which reveals Esther's past.
